Bought himself a boat after the tenth grade.
"I don't think there are many sailors who work in the kindergartens of the country," says Axel Örn Guðmundsson, who does fishing in the summer and studies psychology at the University of Iceland during the winter."
Beach fishing is a very convenient summer job when one is in school.
If fishing is done well, good income can be earned and I find it great to be able to avoid taking student loans.
"The earnings also serve me well into the winter," says Axel Örn Guðmundsson, a 25-year-old psychology student, who goes fishing in the summer like the past summers.
Axel was the newest to dock at Tálknafjörður when a journalist caught up with him late in the evening at the start of the week.
"In the tenth grade I took a boating license for boats under twelve meters and I bought my boat the summer after I finished high school.
I have been fishing in my boat every summer since then.
I bought the boat used from my friend, Hartmann Jónsson, and I named the boat after his name.
Hartmann was already an adult when I bought the boat and had stopped sailing and he was very pleased when he saw that the boat bore his name.
"Hartmann passed away a few years after I took over the boat," says Axel, adding that he bought the boat for three million.
"I made a deal with Hartmann to pay half a million upfront in the beginning of summer and the other half at the end of summer when I was done fishing.
I had the boat debt-free by the end of my first summer on it.”
How could a boy have one and a half million to pay out for a boat when he had just finished high school?
"I had been saving up and collecting money, I had been working with my dad at sea when I was a boy, I was all summers fishing with him and got my share."
I also put my savings into my boat fund.”
Axel was born in Isafjordur, where all his family is from, but he has lived in Kópavogur since he was a boy.
"I can fish here in the west because I have a residence permit with my grandmother in Isafjordur."
I learned in this area here west of rowing with dad.
I travel between fjords depending on how I feel, as this fishing area covers all of the Westfjords.
Although I prefer to be westward, I have also traveled around Snæfellsnes and further.
I have also fished in the south, mostly for grayling,” says Axel, who always casts one early morning and sometimes talks to the seagulls and sings to the sky, in his moments of solitude out on the beach.
"The internet connection out at sea is good, so I can call, listen to podcasts and music.
I don't mind being alone on a boat.
Of course I try to avoid trouble, but certainly something has been afoot at times, but never much danger," says Axel, who is lucky that he is never seasick.
He says the length of the workday depends on how the fishing goes each time.
"In trawling I'm never more than 14 hours fishing in one go, but I've also been fishing in other systems, for example in the lease quota, where I've been continuously fishing for one and a half solar cycles out at sea."
The regulations for beach fishing, he says, are such that he can catch 770 kilos per day, which he finds overwhelming.
"Other restrictions are that I cannot fish on Fridays, Saturdays and Sundays, and I can only fish twelve days a month, during these four months that the coastal fishing season is in effect, in May, June, July and August.
In my opinion, sailors should choose their fishing days according to the weather and nothing else.
This unnecessary pressure is on people to rush instead of having 48 days over the whole summer and being able to choose according to their own will.
"So the zoning could also go my way and areas well situated for fishing should be able to enjoy it," says Axel, who mostly catches cod from the shallow sea on his beach fishing trips, but also occasionally catches some other species of fish.
Axel works over the winter season with his college course at the Núpi daycare in Kópavogur.
"I don't think there are many sailors working in the country's kindergartens," says Axel proudly and adds that he had only intended to work temporarily at the kindergarten.
"I got hooked on it because I find this job amazing.
"I hope that the psychology course will be useful to me in the future at the elementary school level," says Axel, who is also far along with his studies in business.
