Reuters news agency reports that Brumfield's fear is not unfounded.
Figures from a new study commissioned by US authorities show that around 40% of those who died had type 2 diabetes as an underlying condition.
When the ratio of those who had not reached 65 years of age is examined, the ratio increases to one half.
The US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) study took into account more than 10,000 people in 15 countries who died from the coronavirus between February and May.
Jonathan Wortham, an infectious disease specialist at the CDC, says the results are striking, especially for those diagnosed with type 2 diabetes and their loved ones.
